I took part in the AI Buildathon—a hackathon hosted by Elastic and Google Cloud Delhi. 

The problem we picked wasn't glamorous — it was personal. Anyone who's commuted on the Delhi Metro knows the daily chaos: crowded trains, unpredictable delays, no real sense of the best route until you're already stuck in it, and no system for if a person loses their item. So the same things happened to me; I lost my Metro card, which has 500 rupees on it, and I mailed the DMRC on Feb 2026 and got a reply in JUN. Do you really think that person will remember their item after 5 months?

So we built Commutify, an AI travel agent that actually understands how Delhi Metro commuters move and helps them make smarter calls before they even step onto the platform.

We weren't the only ones building something that mattered. 108 participants and 30+ teams showed up for Hackathon New Delhi, all of us building real AI agents on Elastic and Google Cloud across databases, DevOps, and ML/AI. 

Out of that room, three teams walked away as winners. We were lucky enough to be one of them.

Thank you to our team who made this possible: Deep Mishra, ABHINAV.

Respect to the other winning teams too: Orbit-ops by Satyansh Gaur and Saksham Arora, turning environmental data into intelligent decisions; and airDNA by @Aditya Kumar, turning air quality into personalized health intelligence. Different problems, same intensity.

A win like this doesn't happen without the people who show up to make it real. Vikas Chauhan (Cyber Whisper) and Arpan Garg (Commudle) sat through every single submission to pick the best of the best. And our mentors—Ishan Katoch, Saurabh Gupta, Nitish Aggarwal, SHREYASH DHANAWADE, and Anuj Jaiswal—didn't just guide the tech; they actually listened to every team's story before pointing us in the right direction.

